<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 6:20PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Morgan,
southeastern Walton and east central Newton Counties through 645 PM
EDT...
At 619 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Social Circle, or 10
miles east of Covington, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Madison, Social Circle, Rutledge, Bostwick, Herndonville,
Ebenezer, Hard Labor Creek State Park and Brick Store.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
